org.spongepowered.api.text.selector

Class ArgumentTypes

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.spongepowered.api.text.selector.ArgumentTypes

  • public final class ArgumentTypes
extends Object
    Represents the default ArgumentTypes available in Vanilla Minecraft.

    • Field Detail

      • POSITION

        public static final ArgumentHolder.Vector3<com.flowpowered.math.vector.Vector3i,Integer> POSITION
        The argument types representing the position of the selector.

        In Vanilla, this is represented by the x, y and z selector keys.

      • RADIUS

        public static final ArgumentHolder.Limit<ArgumentType<Integer>> RADIUS
        The argument types representing the radius of the selector.

        In Vanilla, this is represented by the r (for minimum) and rm (for maximum) selector keys.

      • GAME_MODE

        public static final ArgumentType<GameMode> GAME_MODE
        The argument type filtering based on the GameMode of a player.

        In Vanilla, this is represented by the m selector key.

        Note that this element is of type ArgumentType.Invertible.

      • COUNT

        public static final ArgumentType<Integer> COUNT
        The argument type limiting the number of results of a Selector. Negative values will reverse the order of targets - for example the farthest targets will be returned first.

        The default count for the SelectorTypes.RANDOM and SelectorTypes.NEAREST_PLAYER is 1, therefore a higher number will increase the count instead of limiting it.

        In Vanilla, this is represented by the c selector key.

      • LEVEL

        public static final ArgumentHolder.Limit<ArgumentType<Integer>> LEVEL
        The argument types filtering based on the number of experience levels of the target.

        In Vanilla, this is represented by the l (for maximum) and lm (for minimum) selector keys.

      • TEAM

        public static final ArgumentType.Invertible<String> TEAM
        The argument type filtering based on the Team of the target. Inverting this argument type will search for all targets not on the specified team instead.

        In Vanilla, this is represented by the team selector key with the ! prefix for inverted values.

      • NAME

        public static final ArgumentType.Invertible<String> NAME
        The argument type filtering based on the name of the target. Inverting this argument type will search for all targets without the specified name instead.

        In Vanilla, this is represented by the name selector key with the ! prefix for inverted values.

      • DIMENSION

        public static final ArgumentHolder.Vector3<com.flowpowered.math.vector.Vector3i,Integer> DIMENSION
        The argument type filtering targets which aren't in the specified volume.

        In Vanilla, this is represented by the dx, dy and dz selector keys.

      • ROTATION

        public static final ArgumentHolder.Limit<ArgumentHolder.Vector3<com.flowpowered.math.vector.Vector3d,Double>> ROTATION
        The argument type filtering targets within a specific rotation range.

        In Vanilla, the Doubles will be floored to Integers and the third float is completely ignored. It is represented by the rx/ry (for minimum) and rxm/rym selector keys.

      • ENTITY_TYPE

        public static final ArgumentType.Invertible<EntityType> ENTITY_TYPE
        The argument type filtering targets based on the EntityType.

        In Vanilla, this is represented by the type selector key.
